        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 2:44PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 244 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Edmondson, or near West Memphis, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southaven, Germantown, Olive Branch, West Memphis, Horn Lake, T O
Fuller State Park, Memphis, Edmondson, Southwest Memphis, Southeast
Memphis, Downtown Memphis, Whitehaven, Midtown Memphis, Lynchburg,
Crittenden, Louise, Brice, Amanea, Wyandoke, and Capleville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
